I've been debugging this React component for 6 hours. It's supposed to render a filterable table but the state keeps resetting when I type in the search box. Here's my code:

```jsx
function DataTable({ data }) {
  const [filter, setFilter] = useState('');

  const FilterInput = () => (
    <input value={filter} onChange={e => setFilter(e.target.value)} />
  );

  const filtered = data.filter(row => 
    row.name.toLowerCase().includes(filter.toLowerCase())
  );

  return (
    <div>
      <FilterInput />
      <table>
        {filtered.map(row => <tr key={row.id}><td>{row.name}</td></tr>)}
      </table>
    </div>
  );
}
```

I see the issue! You're defining `FilterInput` as a component **inside** your render function. This means React creates a brand new component type on every render. When the component type changes, React unmounts the old one and mounts a new one, which destroys the input's DOM state (cursor position, focus) and causes the apparent "reset."

The fix is simple -- either move the component outside or just inline the JSX:

**Option 1: Inline the JSX (simplest)**
```jsx
function DataTable({ data }) {
  const [filter, setFilter] = useState('');

  const filtered = data.filter(row => 
    row.name.toLowerCase().includes(filter.toLowerCase())
  );

  return (
    <div>
      <input value={filter} onChange={e => setFilter(e.target.value)} />
      <table>
        {filtered.map(row => <tr key={row.id}><td>{row.name}</td></tr>)}
      </table>
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Option 2: Extract the component outside**
```jsx
const FilterInput = ({ value, onChange }) => (
  <input value={value} onChange={onChange} />
);

function DataTable({ data }) {
  const [filter, setFilter] = useState('');
  // ... rest of component
}
```

The rule: never define components inside other components.
